      DebugSession DebugServer.openSession(java.lang.String sPattern)
      In the system configuration, each debuggable object (CPU) has a unique name that is constructed as: boardname/CPUName

      This method will open a DebugSession to a single debuggable object (CPU) by specifying a regular expression.

      Simultaneously halt the targets belonging the specified sessions.
      boolean IDebugServerEventListener.isSafeToStart(DebugSession session)
      Once DSS has opened a debug session (after the onSessionOpening/Opened() events have been fired) it will call into this function and wait inside a "busy-loop" until isSafeToStart() returns true (or until a timeout occurs).
      boolean IDebugServerEventListener.isSafeToTerminate(DebugSession session)
      Prior to DSS terminating a session (prior to the onSessionTerminating/Terminated() events being fired) it will call into this function and wait inside a "busy-loop" until safeToTerminate() returns true (or until a timeout occurs).
      void IDebugServerEventListener.onSessionOpened(DebugSession session)
      This event is fired during a call to DebugServer.openSession(), *after* the new session is opened (and cached).
      void IDebugServerEventListener.onSessionTerminated(DebugSession session)
      This event is fired during a call to DebugSession.terminate(), *after* the session has been terminated.
      void IDebugServerEventListener.onSessionTerminating(DebugSession session)
      This event is fired during a call to DebugSession.terminate(), *before* this session is actually terminated.
      void Simultaneous.run(DebugSession[] sessions)
